whereas.text:
Whereas Jeremiah Andrew 
Denton, Jr. (referred to in this preamble as Senator Denton) was born in Mobile, Alabama, on July 15, 1924, and graduated from the United States Naval Academy
			 in 1946;

Whereas Senator Denton is survived by his second wife, Mary Belle Bordone, and his children,
			 Jeremiah A. Denton III, William C. Denton, Donald A. Denton, James S.
			 Denton, Michael C. Denton, Madeleine D. Doak, and Mary D. Lewis;

Whereas Senator Denton was particularly proud of the Denton Program, authorizing the United States military to carry humanitarian aid on a space-available basis to
			 countries in need at no cost to the donor and providing humanitarian aid
			 for almost 30 years;

subparagraph.text:
reiterates the resolute character of Senator Denton as a paragon of bravery who lived a life of
			 honor guided by his values and commitment to the defense of the United
			 States;
